init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States, however, remained in the past.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are still using the same technology, food resources, and ways of living that they used in the 1950s.

actions.text: A committee of the most powerful men in the United States is called together to decide how to handle this dilemma.
